==English==

===Etymology===
# [[Gaelic]] ''[[Mac]]'' (son of) + ''[[Kenzie]]'' ("the intelligent one" or possibly "the wise ruler").  Possible alternate: Gaelic ''[[MacCoinneach]]'' (Son of Kenneth).

===Proper noun===
'''MacKenzie''' ''or'' '''[[Mac Kenzie]]'''
# A [[surname]] of [[Scottish]] origin.

